Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
analyze_ir_paths(25.10)                                analyze_ir_paths(25.10)

Name
       analyze_ir_paths

Syntax
       analyze_ir_paths

       [-help]

       -clock_period <float>

       [-hierarchical_activity_file <string>]

       [-max_slack <float>]

       [-pre_simulation_period <float>]

       -seq_activity <float>

       -simulation_period <float>

       [-user_defined_critical_paths <string>]

       Generates a physical-aware multi-cycle switching activity file contain-
       ing  toggle  information  of  voltage sensitive paths as well as timing
       critical paths in the design for Tempus Power Integrity analysis.  This
       command  generates `swsrc.txt' file in the run directory, which then is
       fed back to the software using the read_activity_file command.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -clock_period <float>
              Specifies the period of dominant clock of the design in  library
              time units. Tempus PI refers to this specified period for multi-
              cycle activity generation.

       -hierarchical_activity_file <string>
              Provides  a mechanism for different sequential activity for sev-
              eral partitions in the design. The  following  is  the  required
              format:

              <hierarchical instance 1> <activity>

              <hierarchical instance 2> <activity>

              ...

       -max_slack <float>
              Specifies  the  maximum slack limit in library time units, above
              which the timing paths are not considered for  activity  genera-
              tion.

       -pre_simulation_period <float>
              Specifies  the pre-simulation duration that will be used by Tem-
              pus PI for activity generation.

              This parameter is useful when package model information is read-
              in using set_package command, as it allows the package  oscilla-
              tions to settle down.

              Note:  The  value  specified must match to value specified under
              set_rail_analysis_mode -record_results_start_time setting.

       -seq_activity <float>
              Specifies the activity of sequential endpoints  in  the  design.
              This  value  will  be used to control the number of IR sensitive
              paths, along with their fanout cone, to toggle in each cycle.

       -simulation_period <float>
              Specifies the simulation period in library time units that  Tem-
              pus  PI  dynamic power analysis will use. The larger the simula-
              tion period, the more will be the number of paths covered in the
              analysis.

              The following formula can be used to set the simulation period:

              sim_cycles = (2/seq_act)*N

              Where,

              * seq_act is the input  sequential  activity  (e.g.,  0.05,  0.1
                etc.)

              * N is the number of nworst paths to be covered per endpoint

              * sim_period is equal to the sim_cycles*<time period of dominant
                clock>

              It  is  recommended to have N>=1, that is, at least one path per
              endpoint should be scheduled in the analysis.

       -user_defined_critical_paths <string>
              Specifies a collection of timing paths that are  to  be  priori-
              tized for toggling while generating Tempus PI activity.

              This  feature is useful when designers have prior information on
              certain timing paths that may switch  together  and  can  poten-
              tially cause IR-induced STA violations.

Examples
              * The  following  command generates the activity file for design
                with dominant clock of 2GHz, with  input  sequential  activity
                being 0.1 and simulation duration being 20ns:

                analyze_ir_paths   -seq_activity   0.1  -simulation_period  20
                -clock_period 0.5

              * The following example specifies different sequential  activity
                for different hierarchical partitions, with 0.2 sequential ac-
                tivity for unspecified partitions and top:

                analyze_ir_paths   -seq_activity   0.2  -simulation_period  30
                -clock_period 0.5 -hierarchical_activity_file hact.txt

                Contents of `hact.txt':

                hierA/inst1 0.25

                hierB/inst2 0.15

              * The following command specifies the  pre-simulation  duration,
                particularly  useful  for  package oscillations to settle when
                package models have been read-in:

                analyze_ir_paths  -seq_activity  0.1   -simulation_period   30
                -clock_period 0.5 -pre_simulation_period 10

